This price decreased on Monday, but remained at a high level, at about 12%.
Goldman Sachs, the only other 'survivor' of the great investment banks on Wall Street after the bankruptcy of Bear Stearns and Lehman Brothers and the purchase of Merrill Lynch, announced last week, 15 billion dollars, partly at Berkshire Hathaway, the group of Warren Buffett.
