Insurance shall determine the fees and payment amounts in case of damage, depending on the health status of the customer, and should the risk be overestimated, the insurance will not be completed at all.
In the past, the customer was sent to a medical examination and the contract was only concluded in knowledge of the results of the investigation.
Ten years ago, Dick invented a much cheaper method: Based on the customer's identification number, he draws the data of the last one and a half years from the pharmacies, which means which preparations were bought, and the program calculates the illness of the customer and what his health is like.
For example, when he regularly buys large amounts of cholesterol-decreasing drugs, it can be concluded that his blood fat levels are untreatedly high, which would automatically turn him into a higher risk group.
